gwt.material.design.client.ui

Class MaterialPushpin

  • java.lang.Object
    • gwt.material.design.client.ui.MaterialPushpin

  • public class MaterialPushpin
extends Object
    Pushpin is our fixed positioning plugin. You can check out our live examples: the fixed Table of Contents on the right.

    UiBinder Usage:

     
 // CAN BE CALLED AS A HELPER STATIC CONTEXT
 MaterialPushpin.apply(target, source.getOffsetHeight() + 600);

 // INSTANTIATE THE PUSHPIN COMPONENT
 MaterialPushpin pushpin = new MaterialPushpin();
 pushpin.setWidget(source);
 pushpin.setTop(300.0);
 pushpin.setOffset(64.0);
 pushpin.setBottom(500.0);
 pushpin.apply();
    Author:
    kevzlou7979

        public static void apply(com.google.gwt.user.client.ui.Widget widget,
                         Double offset)
        A pushpinned element has 3 states. One above and below the scrolling threshold, and the pinned state where the element becomes fixed.
        Parameters:
        widget - - Target widget to apply the pushpin feature
        offset - - The offset from the top the element will be fixed at. (Default: 0)
